Exercise: Experiment with a JavaScript library!
In your Actualize folder, make a new folder called `practice-javascript`. In that folder, make a new file called `index.html` and enter the following code:
```<!DOCTYPE html>
&lt;html lang="en"&gt;
&lt;head&gt;
  &lt;meta charset="UTF-8"&gt;
  &lt;title&gt;JavaScript Example&lt;/title&gt;
&lt;/head&gt;
&lt;body&gt;
  &lt;h1&gt;Hello from HTML!&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;```
To open the HTML file in your browser, run `open index.html` in your terminal


Follow the HighCharts documentation to add a chart: <http://www.highcharts.com/docs>

Once you have a working chart, try to modify the data or make different types of charts!

Bonus: Choose a JavaScript library to experiment with: <https://speckyboy.com/top-50-javascript/>
